ðŸ”’ Intruder (Lockdown)
What To Do

Locks & Lights: Immediately lock the door and turn off all lights.

Get Out of Sight: Move to a part of the room where you cannot be seen through windows or door vision panels.

Total Silence: Silence your phone (turn off vibrate too) and remain absolutely quiet.

Don't Open: Never open the door for anyone; wait for an official "All Clear" from police or school administration.

ðŸ«¨ Earthquake
Facts

Duration: Most shaking lasts only 30 seconds, but it can feel like much longer.

Aftershocks: Smaller quakes can happen minutes or hours after the first one.

Glass: Most injuries are caused by falling glass or furniture, not the building collapsing.

What To Do

Drop: Get down on your hands and knees.

Cover: Get under a sturdy desk or table to protect your head and torso.

Hold On: Grip the leg of the table and stay there until the shaking stops completely.

Stay Inside: Do not run outdoors during the shaking.

ðŸ”” Fire Drill
Facts

Smoke: Most fire-related injuries are caused by breathing in smoke, not the heat.

Speed: A small flame can turn into a major fire in less than 3 minutes.

Doors: Closed doors can stop the spread of fire and keep oxygen away from the flames.

What To Do

Leave Immediately: Drop everything and walk (don't run) to the nearest exit.

Stay Low: If there is smoke, crawl on the floor where the air is cleaner.

Check Doors: Before opening a door, feel it with the back of your hand. If itâ€™s hot, find another way out.

Meeting Point: Go directly to your class's designated meeting spot and stay there for attendance.
